1
00:00:50,760 --> 00:00:57,320


2
00:00:58,120 --> 00:00:59,920
It's my first time
receiving such a surprise.

3
00:01:00,150 --> 00:01:01,700
Hitomi, happy birthday.

4
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:03,300
I'm drowning in happiness.

5
00:01:03,580 --> 00:01:04,500
That's right.

6
00:01:05,390 --> 00:01:06,770
I haven't asked him yet.

7
00:01:07,930 --> 00:01:09,560
I love him so much.

8
00:01:10,840 --> 00:01:11,930
That's why I wanna know.

9
00:01:14,080 --> 00:01:15,420
Can I ask you just one thing?

10
00:01:18,250 --> 00:01:19,020
Shuichi.

11
00:01:21,340 --> 00:01:22,040
Why did Toma

12
00:01:22,970 --> 00:01:23,790
quit theater?

13
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:31,730
Regarding that,

14
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:33,750
I was planning to tell you someday.

15
00:01:35,350 --> 00:01:36,780
I wanted you to know.

16
00:01:38,630 --> 00:01:39,330
Okay.

17
00:01:43,700 --> 00:01:44,400
For ten years.

18
00:01:46,290 --> 00:01:48,650
If I couldn’t land a leading role
in a film within that time,

19
00:01:49,930 --> 00:01:51,160
I'd retire and join the company.

20
00:01:53,850 --> 00:01:55,410
That was my father's condition.

21
00:01:58,310 --> 00:01:59,010
Well.

22
00:01:59,940 --> 00:02:01,890
Maybe I had a rebellious
feeling toward it.

23
00:02:03,860 --> 00:02:05,650
Stepping off the path
my father laid down.

24
00:02:07,300 --> 00:02:08,630
I wanted to become someone.

25
00:02:09,200 --> 00:02:11,290
I know it's the person you know.

26
00:02:11,830 --> 00:02:14,000
Stand up and 20 degrees upward.

27
00:02:14,520 --> 00:02:15,510
Soshu Odawara.

28
00:02:15,910 --> 00:02:17,740
Imagine the city you like.

29
00:02:17,770 --> 00:02:18,750
Imagine the city.

30
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:21,100
At first, I couldn’t do it at all.

31
00:02:22,570 --> 00:02:24,770
That's why I trained so hard.

32
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:26,450
Every single day.

33
00:02:29,640 --> 00:02:30,440
I had a hard time.

34
00:02:31,150 --> 00:02:33,780
It was something I couldn't do.
So I found it fulfilling.

35
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:37,140
I didn't know.

36
00:02:43,650 --> 00:02:46,510
I thought ten years was enough time
to get a chance.

37
00:02:48,030 --> 00:02:49,110
But it isn't that easy.

38
00:02:51,840 --> 00:02:53,700
Being able to debut
is already amazing as it is.

39
00:02:55,010 --> 00:02:56,910
He even went on to play leading roles.

40
00:02:58,370 --> 00:03:00,420
I wonder how much effort
he put into it.

41
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:02,700
And yet

42
00:03:03,270 --> 00:03:04,930
he bet everything on being Toma.

43
00:03:05,880 --> 00:03:06,800
Don't make that face.

44
00:03:07,900 --> 00:03:09,830
I find my current job
fulfilling as well.

45
00:03:12,020 --> 00:03:12,720
But...

46
00:03:15,650 --> 00:03:17,280
I was the one who agreed
with my father.

47
00:03:19,310 --> 00:03:20,300
I made a promise.

48
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,230
That's why I retired

49
00:03:23,850 --> 00:03:24,770
and joined the company.

50
00:03:29,460 --> 00:03:30,160
Are you

51
00:03:31,460 --> 00:03:32,410
truly satisfied?

52
00:03:34,260 --> 00:03:34,990
What?

53
00:03:37,990 --> 00:03:39,600
When you talk about acting,

54
00:03:40,650 --> 00:03:41,740
you looked so happy.

55
00:03:48,720 --> 00:03:49,420
Well.

56
00:03:50,380 --> 00:03:52,750
If you are just forcing yourself

57
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:54,300
then you should...

58
00:03:54,440 --> 00:03:55,370
Go back to being Toma?

59
00:04:00,190 --> 00:04:01,060
I’ve already decided.

60
00:04:06,870 --> 00:04:07,600
I'm sorry.

61
00:04:24,140 --> 00:04:25,460
This was supposed to be

62
00:04:26,730 --> 00:04:27,830
my best birthday ever.

63
00:04:31,740 --> 00:04:33,760
So your birthday ended in awe?

64
00:04:34,130 --> 00:04:34,830
Yeah.

65
00:04:36,110 --> 00:04:36,960
But it's all my fault.

66
00:04:37,750 --> 00:04:39,280
I went overboard and said something.

67
00:04:40,750 --> 00:04:41,580
I get it.

68
00:04:42,210 --> 00:04:45,080
You just want the person you love
to be happy, right?

69
00:04:45,260 --> 00:04:46,260
Exactly.

70
00:04:46,580 --> 00:04:47,470
You really get it.

71
00:04:48,890 --> 00:04:49,590
I got you.

72
00:04:50,580 --> 00:04:51,280
I really do.

73
00:04:51,930 --> 00:04:53,490
You're incredible.

74
00:04:58,300 --> 00:04:59,000
But listen.

75
00:04:59,420 --> 00:05:00,120
Yeah?

76
00:05:03,580 --> 00:05:06,730
Only people who have fallen
deeply in love can understand this.

77
00:05:12,660 --> 00:05:14,450
Those who stay in the shallows

78
00:05:15,270 --> 00:05:17,350
will only think
of their own happiness.

79
00:05:20,460 --> 00:05:22,460
As for us, we know
how to dive deeper into love.

80
00:05:27,690 --> 00:05:28,390
However,

81
00:05:29,340 --> 00:05:32,620
people in the shallow waters
don't drown as easily, you know.

82
00:05:34,550 --> 00:05:35,290
That's deep.

83
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:39,050
Don't leave things awkward
between you two.

84
00:05:40,180 --> 00:05:42,650
You should tell him
how you really feel

85
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:43,830
and make up with him.

86
00:05:47,140 --> 00:05:47,850
Thank you.

87
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:15,850


88
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:35,340
I'll close it.
━Okay.

89
00:06:50,050 --> 00:06:51,370
Please enjoy the meal.

90
00:06:52,950 --> 00:06:53,700
Wow.

91
00:06:54,230 --> 00:06:55,230
It's all my favorites.

92
00:06:56,200 --> 00:06:56,900
Amazing.

93
00:06:58,560 --> 00:06:59,330
I'm caught off guard.

94
00:06:59,930 --> 00:07:00,830
His smile in winter.

95
00:07:01,110 --> 00:07:01,810
It's hard to take.

96
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:04,900
I'll dig in.

97
00:07:05,420 --> 00:07:06,120
Okay.

98
00:07:07,310 --> 00:07:08,150
This character

99
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:10,560
is this from Attack of Shahrazad?

100
00:07:11,090 --> 00:07:12,880
Yes, the one Toma
used to carry around.

101
00:07:13,020 --> 00:07:13,830
It's Poonyan.

102
00:07:14,260 --> 00:07:15,400
So this one must be Pjord.

103
00:07:15,520 --> 00:07:16,220
Yes.

104
00:07:16,320 --> 00:07:18,670
Well, I really love both of them.

105
00:07:19,400 --> 00:07:21,100
It’s a work
I’m personally attached to.

106
00:07:21,730 --> 00:07:22,740
You're so good at it.

107
00:07:22,890 --> 00:07:23,600
It's well made.

108
00:07:23,810 --> 00:07:24,660
Thank you so much.

109
00:07:30,550 --> 00:07:31,250
Well.

110
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,890
I’m sorry about the other day.

111
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:36,070
I overstepped.

112
00:07:38,260 --> 00:07:38,960
Me too.

113
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:42,640
It was your special day.
I’m sorry I ruined the mood.

114
00:07:43,540 --> 00:07:44,240
Don't be.

115
00:07:46,010 --> 00:07:46,710
I...

116
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:47,900
Sir, I...

117
00:07:49,140 --> 00:07:49,840
I mean...

118
00:07:51,220 --> 00:07:52,440
Shuichi, I really

119
00:07:53,250 --> 00:07:53,950
support you.

120
00:07:55,570 --> 00:07:56,270
Thank you.

121
00:07:56,960 --> 00:07:57,760
That means a lot.

122
00:08:00,050 --> 00:08:00,750
Yes.

123
00:08:08,570 --> 00:08:09,300
Poonyan,

124
00:08:10,220 --> 00:08:13,580
is being eaten
by his own master.

125
00:08:15,080 --> 00:08:15,780
So good.

126
00:08:16,770 --> 00:08:17,470
That's a relief.

127
00:08:18,070 --> 00:08:18,800
Then,

128
00:08:18,830 --> 00:08:19,750
Pjord next.

129
00:08:21,110 --> 00:08:21,840
Say ah.

130
00:08:22,370 --> 00:08:23,070
What?

131
00:08:29,280 --> 00:08:30,020
That's so mean.

132
00:08:30,350 --> 00:08:31,180
It hurts.

133
00:08:31,460 --> 00:08:32,460
It hurts so much.

134
00:08:32,890 --> 00:08:34,120
Ouch.

135
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:39,820
Yeah.

136
00:08:40,620 --> 00:08:41,350
I really love him.

137
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:43,520
I'm sorry.

138
00:08:45,860 --> 00:08:46,560
It's Kazuki.

139
00:08:47,260 --> 00:08:47,960
Sorry.

140
00:08:50,290 --> 00:08:50,990
What's up?

141
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:51,980
Toma.

142
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:53,300
Are you free now?

143
00:08:53,690 --> 00:08:54,390
You know...

144
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:56,020
Wait for my response first.

145
00:08:56,810 --> 00:08:57,510
Sorry.

146
00:08:57,970 --> 00:08:59,340
Be the One is next month.

147
00:08:59,520 --> 00:09:00,220
Can you come?

148
00:09:00,510 --> 00:09:03,060
It's turning out really well,
so I want you to see it.

149
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:04,960
Okay. I'll go.

150
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:06,180
Really?

151
00:09:06,620 --> 00:09:07,320
I'll look forward.

152
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:09,300
That's my line.

153
00:09:10,770 --> 00:09:11,550
I'll send an invite.

154
00:09:12,310 --> 00:09:13,010
Sure.

155
00:09:13,140 --> 00:09:13,860
Do your best.

156
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:14,800
I will.

157
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:16,930
Sorry, I have to get back to rehearsal.

158
00:09:17,290 --> 00:09:17,990
Bye.

159
00:09:22,730 --> 00:09:24,360
Be the One is gonna be next month.

160
00:09:25,160 --> 00:09:25,860
Be the One?

161
00:09:26,490 --> 00:09:27,290
I see.

162
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:31,020
But next month we will be busy
preparing for the event.

163
00:09:32,450 --> 00:09:34,100
I gotta make time for him.

164
00:09:34,330 --> 00:09:35,140
He's the lead actor.

165
00:09:38,390 --> 00:09:39,090
Be the One.

166
00:09:39,860 --> 00:09:42,130
Toma used to play the lead role,
and it was a big hit.

167
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:45,910
But now, his predecessor,
Kazuki, is doing it.

168
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:53,560
This is...

169
00:09:53,660 --> 00:09:55,190
Oh my my my.

170
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:57,550
He's lying on my lap?

171
00:09:57,820 --> 00:09:58,550
Celebrate it.

172
00:09:59,230 --> 00:10:02,980
Remember this day to your core.

173
00:10:05,680 --> 00:10:06,620
The breeze feels nice.

174
00:10:08,670 --> 00:10:09,410
Yes.

175
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:10,600
Am I heavy?

176
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:13,440
Not at all.
Your head is very light.

177
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:16,120
Are you saying I'm dumb?

178
00:10:17,040 --> 00:10:17,920
No, that's not

179
00:10:17,940 --> 00:10:18,640
what I meant.

180
00:10:30,140 --> 00:10:30,870
What?

181
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:32,010
Did he fall asleep?

182
00:10:34,020 --> 00:10:34,720
This is bad.

183
00:10:35,380 --> 00:10:37,210
I’ve never seen
his sleeping face before.

184
00:10:38,080 --> 00:10:39,370
He looks so cute.

185
00:10:53,870 --> 00:10:54,570
I wish

186
00:10:55,790 --> 00:10:57,920
moments like this
could last forever.

187
00:11:04,960 --> 00:11:07,470
Regarding the promotional event
for the new Grand Messe.

188
00:11:08,140 --> 00:11:09,980
Today, we will choose the image model.

189
00:11:10,320 --> 00:11:11,670
How about Junya Sakamoto?

190
00:11:12,020 --> 00:11:12,720
What?

191
00:11:13,790 --> 00:11:14,490
You know him?

192
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:15,700
Yes, I do.

193
00:11:16,370 --> 00:11:17,930
Junya Sakamoto, 30 years old.

194
00:11:18,490 --> 00:11:20,380
He is my beloved Toma's

195
00:11:20,420 --> 00:11:21,610
lifelong rival.

196
00:11:22,320 --> 00:11:23,020
Wait up.

197
00:11:23,490 --> 00:11:24,770
Soon Junya Sakamoto will be...

198
00:11:24,870 --> 00:11:25,980
No, within a year.

199
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:28,160
He will become an actor
that everyone will know.

200
00:11:29,270 --> 00:11:29,980
Oh.

201
00:11:29,990 --> 00:11:30,910
I’ve seen him before.

202
00:11:31,270 --> 00:11:33,030
He is a stage play actor.

203
00:11:33,180 --> 00:11:35,300
We rarely see him
in commercials and on TV.

204
00:11:35,700 --> 00:11:36,580
He is famous overseas.

205
00:11:36,820 --> 00:11:38,020
His charisma is insane.

206
00:11:38,290 --> 00:11:39,370
He’s already been cast

207
00:11:39,440 --> 00:11:40,800
in next year’s morning drama.

208
00:11:40,950 --> 00:11:42,790
Soon, he's gonna be famous nationwide.

209
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:44,730
Now is the best time to hire him.

210
00:11:45,830 --> 00:11:46,970
You're so pumped up.

211
00:11:48,170 --> 00:11:49,350
That's not a bad idea at all.

212
00:11:50,810 --> 00:11:53,010
Since he’s not widely known yet,

213
00:11:53,070 --> 00:11:54,820
it means he's fresh
in the eyes of people.

214
00:11:56,020 --> 00:11:57,860
He seems to fit
the brand’s image as well.

215
00:12:00,430 --> 00:12:01,640
If there are no objections,

216
00:12:02,010 --> 00:12:04,140
then we will reach out to him
as soon as possible.

217
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:08,020
It hasn't been decided yet.

218
00:12:18,900 --> 00:12:20,260
Do you like Junya Sakamoto?

219
00:12:20,570 --> 00:12:22,030
I'm totally into him.
He's my fave.

220
00:12:22,750 --> 00:12:23,540
I wonder if Asuka

221
00:12:24,100 --> 00:12:25,640
also knows about Toma.

222
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:28,250
But I just started a month ago.

223
00:12:28,820 --> 00:12:29,520
I see.

224
00:12:30,210 --> 00:12:31,470
So she doesn't know about Toma.

225
00:12:32,690 --> 00:12:33,390
Wait.

226
00:12:33,630 --> 00:12:34,640
Hang on.

227
00:12:35,060 --> 00:12:37,700
If she start looking into Junya’s
past works and everything

228
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:39,460
I'm sure she'll find out about Toma, too.

229
00:12:40,140 --> 00:12:42,340
So person you meant
at the barbecue party was...

230
00:12:42,440 --> 00:12:43,140
It was Junya.

231
00:12:43,630 --> 00:12:44,790
I can't explain it.

232
00:12:45,100 --> 00:12:46,250
But every day just feels

233
00:12:46,730 --> 00:12:47,440
brighter.

234
00:12:48,370 --> 00:12:51,480
Just knowing Junya exists
in the same world as I am,

235
00:12:51,570 --> 00:12:52,920
is enough for me.

236
00:12:53,880 --> 00:12:55,050
I know that feeling so well.

237
00:12:57,790 --> 00:12:58,490
See?

238
00:12:58,570 --> 00:13:00,290
I just took one step closer to Junya.

239
00:13:00,730 --> 00:13:02,770
No. You might be actually
drifting away from him.

240
00:13:02,870 --> 00:13:03,570
Never.

241
00:13:04,140 --> 00:13:05,040
If I keep on walking,

242
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:07,650
I know someday I'll reach Junya.

243
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:12,470
Because the earth is round, after all.

244
00:13:14,550 --> 00:13:15,300
What happened?

245
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:16,660
Well.

246
00:13:17,270 --> 00:13:17,970
That's deep.

247
00:13:34,870 --> 00:13:36,980
Isn’t Junya arriving very soon,
Ms. Asuka?

248
00:13:37,090 --> 00:13:38,020
What?
Already?

249
00:13:55,830 --> 00:13:56,530
Are you okay?

250
00:13:58,370 --> 00:14:00,060
I-I'm not okay.

251
00:14:03,890 --> 00:14:04,890
His aura is amazing.

252
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:06,140
Yeah.

253
00:14:06,150 --> 00:14:07,040
Oh my.

254
00:14:07,560 --> 00:14:09,490
Thank you for coming all this way.

255
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:10,860
We've been waiting.

256
00:14:11,170 --> 00:14:13,700
Nice to meet you.
I'm Kiyama from TKG Company.

257
00:14:14,740 --> 00:14:15,440
I'm Takagi.

258
00:14:16,700 --> 00:14:17,400
Nice to meet you.

259
00:14:18,880 --> 00:14:19,580
Hello.

260
00:14:20,250 --> 00:14:21,040
Nice to meet you.

261
00:14:28,750 --> 00:14:30,310
For the unveiling event

262
00:14:30,410 --> 00:14:32,230
of the Gran Messe new store.

263
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:35,410
Our partner brand would like someone
with a strong charisma like you

264
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:36,580
to be the image model.

265
00:14:37,450 --> 00:14:38,600
We would be very grateful

266
00:14:38,630 --> 00:14:40,760
if you could lend us your support,
Mr. Sakamoto.

267
00:14:44,520 --> 00:14:45,610
Wait.

268
00:14:46,900 --> 00:14:47,700
Where?
━What?

269
00:14:47,900 --> 00:14:48,840
Where did he touch?

270
00:14:48,970 --> 00:14:49,900
Oh, it's here.

271
00:14:51,060 --> 00:14:52,980
It's an indirect touch
with Junya's palm.

272
00:14:53,070 --> 00:14:54,750
Stop it.

273
00:14:54,920 --> 00:14:55,950
It's mine.

274
00:14:55,980 --> 00:14:56,710
Hang on.

275
00:14:56,740 --> 00:14:57,440
You too?

276
00:14:57,850 --> 00:14:58,560
Yeah.

277
00:14:58,720 --> 00:14:59,420
Junya in person.

278
00:14:59,670 --> 00:15:01,710
Especially when he's up close,
it was breathtaking.

279
00:15:01,890 --> 00:15:02,610
I know, right?

280
00:15:02,630 --> 00:15:04,260
I hope he agrees to our offer.

281
00:15:04,340 --> 00:15:05,820
I want him to accept it.

282
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:07,370
Shuichi.

283
00:15:08,680 --> 00:15:10,010
I wonder how he feels right now.

284
00:15:11,420 --> 00:15:12,460
They used to be rivals.

285
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:13,800
But now...

286
00:15:13,840 --> 00:15:14,930
Manager is cooler, right?

287
00:15:15,890 --> 00:15:16,590
Yeah.

288
00:15:28,270 --> 00:15:29,390
Pleased to work with you.

289
00:15:30,430 --> 00:15:31,130
Likewise.

290
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:32,270
Thank you so much.

291
00:15:34,920 --> 00:15:35,780
I'll escort you.

292
00:15:47,950 --> 00:15:48,650
Go on without me.

293
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:49,420
Yes, sir.

294
00:15:55,090 --> 00:15:57,290
Working with you
in this environment

295
00:15:58,170 --> 00:15:59,230
feels strange.

296
00:16:01,940 --> 00:16:03,260
I heard you got the morning drama.

297
00:16:03,920 --> 00:16:04,620
Congrats.

298
00:16:06,140 --> 00:16:07,110
Are you a stranger?

299
00:16:13,030 --> 00:16:15,480
How long are you going
to keep playing "Salaryman A"?

300
00:16:16,580 --> 00:16:17,280
What?

301
00:16:18,700 --> 00:16:19,850
Is this a stage?

302
00:16:20,820 --> 00:16:22,380
Where are the cameras?

303
00:16:22,820 --> 00:16:23,520
Stop it.

304
00:16:24,150 --> 00:16:25,680
This is where I belong now.

305
00:16:26,630 --> 00:16:27,330
No.

306
00:16:29,420 --> 00:16:30,900
You are Toma Kiryu.

307
00:16:35,100 --> 00:16:37,010
I always felt that your presence
was a nuisance.

308
00:16:38,140 --> 00:16:40,010
You were always a step ahead of me.

309
00:16:42,730 --> 00:16:44,400
I wished for you to disappear.

310
00:16:45,480 --> 00:16:46,510
Then your wish is granted.

311
00:16:46,990 --> 00:16:47,690
Don't mock me.

312
00:16:52,580 --> 00:16:54,170
That wouldn’t mean anything.

313
00:16:55,430 --> 00:16:57,880
As far as I’m concerned,
our rivalry isn’t over

314
00:17:00,180 --> 00:17:01,540
But we're in different worlds now.

315
00:17:02,960 --> 00:17:04,660
I find it comforting
when I see you act.

316
00:17:04,970 --> 00:17:05,690
Don’t play dumb.

317
00:17:08,730 --> 00:17:09,430
Listen.

318
00:17:10,260 --> 00:17:11,730
You're just lying to yourself.

319
00:17:11,820 --> 00:17:13,360
You keep yourself busy to avoid it.

320
00:17:20,140 --> 00:17:20,850
Come back,

321
00:17:21,970 --> 00:17:22,690
Toma.

322
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:35,350
I'm looking forward
to working with you on this event.

323
00:17:49,730 --> 00:17:50,770


324
00:17:54,890 --> 00:17:58,210


325
00:17:58,240 --> 00:18:00,290


326
00:18:00,820 --> 00:18:02,990


327
00:18:04,080 --> 00:18:05,340
Thank you for your hard work.

328
00:18:06,820 --> 00:18:07,520
Here you go.

329
00:18:09,720 --> 00:18:10,420
Thank you.

330
00:18:11,430 --> 00:18:12,130
Sure.

331
00:18:13,100 --> 00:18:14,620
I'll be leaving first.

332
00:18:15,100 --> 00:18:15,840
Take care.

333
00:18:15,930 --> 00:18:16,630
Okay.

334
00:18:23,780 --> 00:18:25,110
Junya might be right.

335
00:18:26,300 --> 00:18:27,130
Maybe Shuichi

336
00:18:28,060 --> 00:18:29,520
is really just keeping himself busy

337
00:18:30,110 --> 00:18:31,930
to avoid facing what he really wants.

338
00:18:46,750 --> 00:18:49,440
<i></i>

339
00:18:52,930 --> 00:18:53,980
<Sure.>

340
00:18:56,120 --> 00:18:56,820
I wonder.

341
00:18:57,450 --> 00:18:58,970
How he feels if he watch Kazuki's play

342
00:19:00,190 --> 00:19:00,890
right now?

343
00:19:22,220 --> 00:19:22,920
Okay.

344
00:19:29,320 --> 00:19:30,960
It might be best for Shuichi

345
00:19:32,070 --> 00:19:34,550
if he fails to make it in today's show.

346
00:19:40,050 --> 00:19:40,880
I made it in time.

347
00:19:47,270 --> 00:19:47,980
I get it now.

348
00:19:50,020 --> 00:19:50,720
I...

349
00:19:51,840 --> 00:19:53,110
This is who I am.

350
00:20:09,490 --> 00:20:10,220
A guy like me

351
00:20:11,180 --> 00:20:12,820
might not be able to change the world.

352
00:20:13,760 --> 00:20:14,460
However,

353
00:20:15,380 --> 00:20:16,940
I can change myself.

354
00:20:18,420 --> 00:20:19,120
That is why

355
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:21,170
I will never

356
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:24,080
give up on myself.

357
00:20:55,620 --> 00:20:56,320
Hey.

358
00:20:57,110 --> 00:20:58,030
How do you feel?

359
00:20:59,050 --> 00:21:00,350
When you watch this stage?

360
00:21:05,880 --> 00:21:06,580
Hello everyone.

361
00:21:06,960 --> 00:21:08,650
Thank you for coming
to see the show.

362
00:21:09,510 --> 00:21:10,210
This is

363
00:21:10,840 --> 00:21:11,890
my first lead role.

364
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:14,210
I was full of anxiety.

365
00:21:15,120 --> 00:21:15,820
But then,

366
00:21:16,860 --> 00:21:20,020
I asked for advice from a senior
who once to played the same role.

367
00:21:21,530 --> 00:21:22,300
He said,

368
00:21:23,940 --> 00:21:25,050
"I know you can do it."

369
00:21:26,070 --> 00:21:27,750
He gently pushed me forward.

370
00:21:28,910 --> 00:21:30,930
He even gave me advice
on how I should act.

371
00:21:32,710 --> 00:21:34,800
That senior is no longer in theater.

372
00:21:37,120 --> 00:21:37,820
Even until now,

373
00:21:38,640 --> 00:21:39,580
he's someone I respect.

374
00:21:40,340 --> 00:21:41,380
He is my beloved senior.

375
00:21:43,160 --> 00:21:44,200
I'll keep working hard

376
00:21:44,840 --> 00:21:46,430
so he can see how much I’ve grown.

377
00:21:46,840 --> 00:21:47,560
I'll do my best.

378
00:21:58,620 --> 00:21:59,680
Kazuki really did his best.

379
00:22:00,270 --> 00:22:00,970
Yes.

380
00:22:01,410 --> 00:22:02,220
The line,

381
00:22:02,520 --> 00:22:04,770
"I love you so much it makes me sigh.
I’m hopelessly undone."

382
00:22:04,810 --> 00:22:05,870
changed a bit, right?

383
00:22:06,670 --> 00:22:07,440
Impressive.

384
00:22:08,690 --> 00:22:09,390
Yes.

385
00:22:09,770 --> 00:22:11,340
I want Toma to say it.

386
00:22:11,360 --> 00:22:14,540
"I love you so much it makes me sigh.
I’m hopelessly undone."

387
00:22:14,550 --> 00:22:15,950
Please say it.

388
00:22:18,100 --> 00:22:18,800
It's Kazuki.

389
00:22:20,930 --> 00:22:21,650
Hello?

390
00:22:22,090 --> 00:22:24,100
Why didn't you come
to the dressing room?

391
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:28,280
I thought the final day would be busy
with the people involved in the show.

392
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:30,630
But you are involved
in this show as well.

393
00:22:31,790 --> 00:22:32,770
No, I'm not.

394
00:22:33,740 --> 00:22:34,640
You said so too.

395
00:22:35,580 --> 00:22:37,590
Toma no longer exist in that world.

396
00:22:40,960 --> 00:22:41,890
What are you saying?

397
00:22:43,960 --> 00:22:45,750
To be honest, I want you back.

398
00:22:49,230 --> 00:22:50,140
I want to chase

399
00:22:51,600 --> 00:22:52,670
behind Toma's back again.

400
00:22:56,300 --> 00:22:57,000
Hey.

401
00:22:57,540 --> 00:22:59,160
I'll keep on waiting
until Toma returns.

402
00:23:06,510 --> 00:23:09,260
Thank you so much, everyone,
for coming by today.

403
00:23:09,620 --> 00:23:11,920
Please allow me to start this event.

404
00:23:39,080 --> 00:23:39,780
I knew it.

405
00:23:40,820 --> 00:23:42,750
This is the place where
Shuichi really belongs.

406
00:24:47,490 --> 00:24:48,590
That naughty smile.

407
00:24:48,720 --> 00:24:50,120
I'm gonna save it forever in my core.

408
00:24:50,180 --> 00:24:51,720
I became your fan.

409
00:24:52,180 --> 00:24:53,020
What are you?

410
00:24:53,880 --> 00:24:55,710
My bias becoming my manager
then my lover.

411
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:57,340
It was never possible.

412
00:24:57,750 --> 00:24:59,470
All of these
were part of my imagination.
